The purpose of this research is to address the phenomenon of plasticity loss in deep reinforcement learning agents, where neural networks lose their ability to learn effectively over time. This persistent challenge significantly hinders the long-term performance and adaptability of RL agents in dynamic environments. Existing approaches often rely on architectural modifications or hyperparameter tuning, which can be computationally expensive.
